WEBVTT

00:00.912 --> 00:03.149
♪ ♪

00:04.653 --> 00:08.594
♪ Those fingers in my hair ♪

00:08.628 --> 00:12.201
♪ That sly come-hither stare ♪

00:12.234 --> 00:15.374
♪ That strips
my conscience bare ♪

00:15.407 --> 00:19.282
♪ It's witchcraft ♪

00:19.315 --> 00:23.189
♪ And I've got no defense
for it ♪

00:23.223 --> 00:26.362
♪ The heat is too intense
for it ♪

00:26.396 --> 00:32.441
♪ What good would
common sense for it do? ♪

00:32.474 --> 00:35.648
♪ 'Cause it's witchcraft ♪

00:35.682 --> 00:40.357
♪ Wicked witchcraft ♪

00:40.390 --> 00:43.430
-♪ Although I know that... ♪
-No, no, no, no, no.

00:43.463 --> 00:48.073
Uh, it w... it was great
until you did that nasal thing.

00:48.106 --> 00:50.578
I need you to be
an authentic replica of me

00:50.612 --> 00:53.584
and not a rude impersonation.

00:53.618 --> 00:57.124
Okay, let's take ten, and then
we'll run the whole show.

00:57.157 --> 00:58.460
You, a word.

01:02.736 --> 01:04.305
(door closes in distance)

01:04.338 --> 01:06.276
I'm keeping all the nightly
performance fees,

01:06.309 --> 01:09.215
but what tips you make
are yours from now on.

01:09.248 --> 01:11.687
The honor to perform as you
is enough payment alone.

01:11.720 --> 01:14.493
-(phone ringing)
-(chuckles) Cut the bullshit.

01:14.526 --> 01:16.497
You're doing me a solid here,

01:16.530 --> 01:18.266
but I've got better things to do
than sing background

01:18.300 --> 01:20.404
for blow jobs and teabagging.

01:20.437 --> 01:21.674
So, the new business is
going well?

01:21.707 --> 01:22.876
Hardly.

01:22.909 --> 01:24.780
Kathy, you have a phone call.

01:24.813 --> 01:27.251
-Sounds urgent.
-See what I mean?

01:27.284 --> 01:28.721
Nonstop.

01:31.760 --> 01:33.731
Hello?

01:35.267 --> 01:38.473
You've got to be
fucking kidding me.

01:38.507 --> 01:40.545
(distant indistinct shouting)

01:45.655 --> 01:48.393
♪ ♪

01:51.500 --> 01:53.269
(horn honks)

01:56.744 --> 01:58.814
(horn honks in distance)

02:00.918 --> 02:03.591
♪ ♪

02:12.676 --> 02:14.846
(entry bell chiming)

02:17.184 --> 02:18.788
KATHY:
We're closed.

02:18.821 --> 02:20.892
The sign outside says
you're open.

02:20.925 --> 02:24.365
Ugh! I forgot to turn it around.

02:24.398 --> 02:26.503
Both my psychics quit on me
this week.

02:26.537 --> 02:28.373
You want your fortune told,

02:28.406 --> 02:30.410
order something from the Chinese
restaurant across the street.

02:30.444 --> 02:32.281
I don't want my fortune told.

02:32.314 --> 02:34.452
I came in because of
the help wanted sign.

02:34.485 --> 02:36.422
Are you willing to work
a night shift,

02:36.456 --> 02:37.726
10:00 to 3:00?

02:37.759 --> 02:39.228
2:00 is when
all the boys come out,

02:39.261 --> 02:41.265
and they love talking
with readers.

02:41.299 --> 02:43.269
Get a few drinks in them,
and suddenly

02:43.303 --> 02:45.474
they want to know the future.

02:45.508 --> 02:47.344
It's getting crazier lately.

02:47.378 --> 02:49.215
I wouldn't be surprised
if it had something to do

02:49.248 --> 02:50.685
with all the disappearances.

02:50.718 --> 02:52.221
I'll do whatever it takes.

02:52.254 --> 02:53.456
I need a paying job.

02:53.491 --> 02:55.728
I'm Fran.

02:55.762 --> 02:57.966
Do you have any experience
with tarot cards, Fran?

02:57.999 --> 02:59.936
Not really.

02:59.970 --> 03:01.940
I'll take that as a no.

03:01.974 --> 03:03.911
(Kathy sighs)

03:08.587 --> 03:10.758
You need to fill this out.

03:10.792 --> 03:12.361
Tarot deck plus instructions.

03:12.394 --> 03:13.864
Come back tomorrow night

03:13.898 --> 03:15.467
with a decent working knowledge
of the cards,

03:15.501 --> 03:17.872
I'll start you right up.

03:17.906 --> 03:19.609
Don't you want to know
if I'm a psychic?

03:19.643 --> 03:22.582
I already know.
It doesn't exist.

03:22.615 --> 03:24.853
If psychics were real,
they'd be millionaires

03:24.886 --> 03:27.692
from playing the stock market.

03:27.726 --> 03:30.230
This is entertainment, honey.

03:30.263 --> 03:31.767
A carnival show.

03:31.800 --> 03:34.840
Cheaper than a shrink
and guaranteed to make your day.

03:34.873 --> 03:37.444
Oh, the most important thing is
that the customer leaves

03:37.478 --> 03:39.415
feeling better
than when they came in,

03:39.448 --> 03:41.954
so no bad news.

03:41.987 --> 03:44.793
(gasps) Crazy wealth.

03:44.826 --> 03:46.797
Trip to Paris.

03:46.830 --> 03:50.003
(gasps) Romance with the guy
or gal of their dreams.

03:50.036 --> 03:52.642
Do that and you're gold.

03:52.675 --> 03:56.382
By lying to vulnerable folk
who are desperate for help?

03:56.416 --> 03:58.621
By telling them
what they want to hear.

03:58.654 --> 04:00.858
What, you think they walk in
to learn they have lung cancer?

04:00.892 --> 04:03.396
They want a reason
to get up in the morning.

04:03.430 --> 04:05.300
Well, I've never been one
to fake an orgasm,

04:05.333 --> 04:08.473
let alone fake optimism
about the state of the world.

04:08.507 --> 04:10.410
You know, actually,

04:10.444 --> 04:12.749
I think I might be
a little bit psychic.

04:12.782 --> 04:14.653
Sometimes I have these dreams,

04:14.686 --> 04:16.924
and then I read about something
in the paper the next day...

04:16.957 --> 04:18.994
That's fascinating, Kreskin.

04:20.665 --> 04:22.334
See you tomorrow?

04:27.444 --> 04:29.816
FRAN:
I mean, on the one hand,
this seems kind of sleazy,

04:29.850 --> 04:32.287
but on the other hand,
what she says makes sense.

04:32.321 --> 04:33.624
It's entertainment.

04:33.657 --> 04:36.997
I mean, that's what movies
and TV shows do.

04:37.030 --> 04:39.636
I mean, the last part of
the hour of Trapper John,

04:39.669 --> 04:42.307
he always saves
the sick little girl.

04:42.341 --> 04:43.944
Well, I guess you talked
yourself into it.

04:43.978 --> 04:45.013
FRAN (over phone):
All right,

04:45.046 --> 04:46.884
what do you think?

04:46.917 --> 04:49.488
I think you need the money,
and this sounds like a good gig.

04:49.523 --> 04:51.560
I mean, you can't live
on freelancing at The Native.

04:51.593 --> 04:53.831
Figure out the fucking
tarot cards yet?

04:53.864 --> 04:56.002
I can't tell The Devil
from The Hanged Man,

04:56.035 --> 04:57.705
but I'll get it.

04:57.739 --> 04:59.074
And I need something to get me

04:59.108 --> 05:00.711
through this shitty summer.

05:00.745 --> 05:03.016
Well, I got something
that can get you through.

05:03.049 --> 05:05.988
Come over here.
Let me tear off your clothes.

05:06.022 --> 05:07.625
No. No... (chuckles)

05:07.659 --> 05:10.063
No. I've got to study
these cards.

05:10.096 --> 05:12.569
I mean, I at least have to
make it look good.

05:12.602 --> 05:15.340
But you know what? I'll come by
before work and say hi, okay?

05:15.373 --> 05:17.044
And maybe I'll even give you
a free reading.

05:17.077 --> 05:18.981
(laughing)

05:19.014 --> 05:20.985
-Bye.
-(dial tone drones)

05:23.924 --> 05:25.928
♪ ♪

05:27.364 --> 05:29.401
(siren wailing)

05:43.998 --> 05:46.570
♪ ♪

05:55.020 --> 05:57.892
♪ ♪

06:25.781 --> 06:27.919
♪ ♪

07:00.818 --> 07:03.456
Everyone s

07:03.489 --> 07:05.895
Hormones pumping,
making you crazy.

07:05.928 --> 07:10.504
But I've never been more
centered or happier,

07:10.538 --> 07:12.609
despite everything
that's going on.

07:12.642 --> 07:14.579
Probably 'cause you're already
a little crazy to begin with.

07:14.613 --> 07:16.883
The hormones just sort of
level you out.

07:16.917 --> 07:18.687
(chuckles)

07:18.721 --> 07:20.190
You're gonna be a great mom,
face it.

07:20.223 --> 07:21.893
That's a lucky kid.

07:21.927 --> 07:24.465
Especially since it won't
have me as a father.

07:24.499 --> 07:27.137
Well, technically
you are the father.

07:27.170 --> 07:28.841
-(heavy breathing)
-(laughs)

07:28.874 --> 07:30.811
(imitates Darth Vader):
I am your father.

07:30.845 --> 07:33.082
(laughing):
What are you doing?

07:33.116 --> 07:34.686
Correction,
I am the sperm donor,

07:34.719 --> 07:36.055
and I'm perfectly happy
about that.

07:36.088 --> 07:38.059
What do you think it's gonna be?

07:38.092 --> 07:40.163
A boy or a girl?

07:40.196 --> 07:41.867
What if we don't have to guess?

07:41.900 --> 07:43.837
(groans) I don't believe
in that stuff.

07:43.871 --> 07:45.708
Let's go in, it'll be fun.

07:45.741 --> 07:47.110
Come on.

07:47.144 --> 07:48.647
-(blows raspberry)
-(door opens)

07:48.681 --> 07:50.584
(entry bell chimes)

07:52.522 --> 07:53.757
-(door closes)
-(entry bell chimes)

07:53.791 --> 07:55.594
Oh. Hi.

07:55.628 --> 07:57.498
Fran?

07:57.532 --> 07:59.703
-What are you doing here?
-I work here now.

07:59.736 --> 08:01.005
Wait, don't you work
at The Native?

08:01.038 --> 08:02.909
Well, I write some articles
for them.

08:02.942 --> 08:05.280
(scoffs) Somebody had
to get the word out.

08:05.313 --> 08:08.019
Fortune telling, government
conspiracy theories...

08:08.052 --> 08:09.923
I'm guessing you're
a UFO fanatic as well.

08:09.956 --> 08:12.160
Everything I told you
about Plumb Island is

08:12.194 --> 08:14.064
the God's honest truth.

08:14.098 --> 08:17.137
Did you even bother following up
on any of the leads I gave you?

08:17.170 --> 08:19.743
What are you two
even talking about?

08:19.776 --> 08:21.145
I've been looking into
some of it.

08:21.178 --> 08:22.615
Then maybe we've been brought

08:22.648 --> 08:23.784
back together again
for a reason.

08:23.817 --> 08:25.988
This place draws you in.

08:26.022 --> 08:28.494
It chose you
just the way it chose me.

08:29.294 --> 08:32.067
Okay. (scoffs)
Let's get out of here.

08:33.169 --> 08:35.273
FRAN:
You're with child.

08:35.306 --> 08:36.743
Well, that much is obvious.

08:36.777 --> 08:39.014
But that question in your heart,

08:39.048 --> 08:41.152
I can tell you what it is
you want to know.

08:44.158 --> 08:46.930
(takes slow, deep breath)

08:47.932 --> 08:49.134
Fuck it.

08:49.168 --> 08:51.272
One card, one chance,

08:51.305 --> 08:52.842
and then we're out of here.

09:01.993 --> 09:03.931
Okay.

09:03.964 --> 09:05.266
(Fran exhales)

09:06.368 --> 09:08.306
That question that you have...

09:10.110 --> 09:11.947
...hold it in your mind
while you cut the deck.

09:11.980 --> 09:14.853
It's important to have
that energy in the cards.

09:14.886 --> 09:16.923
(Hannah chuckles)

09:26.308 --> 09:28.212
Huh, the queen of pentacles.
Okay.

09:28.246 --> 09:29.849
(Hannah scoffing)

09:29.883 --> 09:32.187
-What's it mean?
-It's been a little while.

09:32.220 --> 09:36.128
Oh, okay, pentacles are
connected to the earth.

09:36.162 --> 09:38.967
So that should be good, I think.

09:39.001 --> 09:40.571
Good for what?

09:41.338 --> 09:44.144
Uh... the ten of swords.

09:44.178 --> 09:47.885
Hmm. What's that mean?

09:47.919 --> 09:50.323
Okay, forget about that card.
Never mind.

09:50.356 --> 09:51.927
Okay, come on, let's go.

09:51.960 --> 09:53.697
No, no, no. No. No. No, wait.

09:53.730 --> 09:56.135
Ah, The Empress.

09:56.168 --> 09:58.874
This is connected
to feminine energy.

09:58.907 --> 10:02.147
Have you been wishing
for a daughter?

10:02.180 --> 10:03.717
I'm not sure.

10:03.750 --> 10:06.055
FRAN:
The cards always tell the truth.

10:06.088 --> 10:08.259
I don't know how they do it,
but they do.

10:08.292 --> 10:10.698
Listen, for ten bucks,

10:10.731 --> 10:12.000
I'll answer
anything you want to know.

10:12.033 --> 10:13.971
No, I'm-I'm good.

10:14.004 --> 10:15.741
Come on. You're the one

10:15.774 --> 10:17.377
who wanted to come here
in the first place.

10:17.410 --> 10:19.114
(cards shuffling)

10:19.148 --> 10:20.350
Fine.

10:27.732 --> 10:30.136
(Fran clears throat)

10:30.170 --> 10:32.942
ADAM:
I lost a friend recently.

10:32.975 --> 10:36.315
We're not even sure he's dead,
but he's been missing,

10:36.348 --> 10:38.286
and with all the murders...

10:38.319 --> 10:39.989
FRAN:
Say no more.

10:55.955 --> 10:59.228
Okay, the Death card
doesn't mean literal death.

10:59.261 --> 11:01.232
It can mean the end of one part
of your friend's life

11:01.265 --> 11:03.937
-and the beginning of another.
-I don't want to do this.

11:06.776 --> 11:08.079
Okay.

11:08.112 --> 11:10.083
Let's go back to Hannah.

11:10.116 --> 11:12.722
Energy transfer and all that.

11:19.836 --> 11:22.742
♪ ♪

11:29.454 --> 11:31.927
What are the odds of that
happening?

11:31.960 --> 11:33.162
Hmm.

11:34.231 --> 11:36.168
I mean, that makes no sense.

11:36.202 --> 11:38.105
There's-there's only
one Death card per deck.

11:38.139 --> 11:39.876
Whatever you're doing,
this isn't funny.

11:39.909 --> 11:41.378
I'm not doing anything.

11:41.412 --> 11:43.416
Yes, you are,
you're upsetting my friend.

11:44.919 --> 11:46.790
FRAN:
This doesn't make any sense.

11:46.823 --> 11:48.760
What kind of business do you
think you're running here? Huh?

11:48.794 --> 11:50.463
Please don't go. There's got to
be some kind of an explanation.

11:50.497 --> 11:52.902
Upsetting a pregnant woman. Huh?

11:52.935 --> 11:54.438
Come on. We're going.

11:54.471 --> 11:56.308
Let's go.

11:56.342 --> 11:59.414
I'm sorry. Come on.
I'm sorry.

12:01.018 --> 12:02.722
(entry bell chimes)

12:03.523 --> 12:04.826
(door closes)

12:11.272 --> 12:13.309
(water running)

12:24.097 --> 12:26.101
(sighs)

12:31.980 --> 12:33.517
Are you okay?

12:33.550 --> 12:36.021
Um, I think I had
some bad sushi,

12:36.055 --> 12:37.525
and I got a parasite
or something.

12:37.558 --> 12:39.963
I haven't been able to keep
anything down for weeks.

12:39.996 --> 12:41.332
ATTORNEY:
Isn't that concerning?

12:41.365 --> 12:43.302
Maybe we can hold off
on the diagnosis

12:43.336 --> 12:45.741
until after the parties
have signed.

12:53.022 --> 12:55.059
♪ ♪

13:02.508 --> 13:04.011
(muffled):
Honey?

13:05.013 --> 13:07.450
Are you okay?

13:10.356 --> 13:12.427
(normal volume):
Honey?

13:15.868 --> 13:17.972
Do you think you could just
give us a moment?

13:22.180 --> 13:23.984
(Barbara sighs softly)

13:29.394 --> 13:31.298
-What is it?
-I don't know. I just...

13:31.332 --> 13:34.137
Please don't do this, Barbara.

13:34.171 --> 13:36.175
This is the right thing.
You know it is.

13:36.208 --> 13:37.978
No, I don't know it,
that's the problem.

13:38.012 --> 13:40.249
Just throwing everything away
like this,

13:40.283 --> 13:43.523
it just feels like we're making
a terrible mistake.

13:43.557 --> 13:47.063
It's more than that.
We don't have a marriage.

13:47.097 --> 13:48.600
Who cares if we don't do
all the things

13:48.633 --> 13:50.604
that husbands and wives
are supposed to do?

13:50.637 --> 13:53.409
I want more than that.

13:53.442 --> 13:55.246
So should you.

13:56.482 --> 14:00.123
Honey,
we will always be friends.

14:00.156 --> 14:03.329
We will always,
always care for each other.

14:03.362 --> 14:05.968
But...

14:06.001 --> 14:09.107
we cannot stay married, Barbara.
We cannot.

14:10.644 --> 14:11.980
I can't.

14:12.013 --> 14:13.583
(softly):
Oh, God.

14:13.617 --> 14:16.890
Look, I know...

14:16.923 --> 14:18.426
I know you're scared.

14:18.459 --> 14:21.900
But you will find
somebody perfect for you.

14:24.672 --> 14:27.545
We need to do this, honey.

14:31.218 --> 14:32.955
We need to.

14:32.988 --> 14:35.293
For both our sakes.

14:36.496 --> 14:40.169
Well, one thing hasn't changed.

14:41.606 --> 14:43.643
I still want you to be happy.

14:43.677 --> 14:45.881
I feel the same for you.

14:49.989 --> 14:51.993
♪ ♪

15:05.353 --> 15:08.259
(Barbara breathing heavily)

15:09.261 --> 15:11.633
Oh, God. Honey?

15:11.666 --> 15:13.436
Honey?

15:13.469 --> 15:14.972
Hey!

15:15.974 --> 15:18.012
(indistinct announcement
over P. A. in distance)

15:22.020 --> 15:23.590
Where am I?

15:23.623 --> 15:25.994
In the hospital.
You passed out.

15:26.028 --> 15:27.698
-I did?
-Right after you signed.

15:27.731 --> 15:29.101
Whacked your head on the floor.

15:29.134 --> 15:30.971
Scared the shit out of me.

15:31.004 --> 15:32.508
(groaning)

15:34.645 --> 15:37.618
-I'm sorry.
-No, come on. It's my fault.

15:37.651 --> 15:40.022
I pushed way too hard.

15:40.056 --> 15:43.229
No, I'm sorry that I need you
to do something for me.

15:43.262 --> 15:46.168
I, uh, did something terrible.

15:46.201 --> 15:48.239
What?

15:48.272 --> 15:50.143
I got a dog.

15:51.478 --> 15:53.015
What's so terrible about that?

15:53.048 --> 15:54.685
He's a papillon.

15:54.719 --> 15:56.321
But wait until you meet him.

15:56.355 --> 15:58.425
He's so cute,
but he's been inside all day,

15:58.459 --> 16:00.029
and he hasn't had
anything to eat.

16:00.062 --> 16:01.465
I'm sure he's peed
all over the apartment.

16:01.499 --> 16:04.204
Okay. Say no more.

16:04.237 --> 16:05.641
-You don't mind?
-I do.

16:05.674 --> 16:07.277
But I'll go anyway,

16:07.310 --> 16:08.680
because despite everything

16:08.713 --> 16:10.416
we're still gonna be there
for each other.

16:10.449 --> 16:11.953
Thank you.

16:13.255 --> 16:14.257
Ow.

16:14.291 --> 16:16.295
(barking)

16:24.077 --> 16:25.313
Hey, puppy.

16:26.315 --> 16:28.319
(switch clicking)

16:29.321 --> 16:31.291
(barking)

16:31.325 --> 16:32.628
What are you yapping at, huh?

16:32.661 --> 16:35.701
I'm Mommy's friend.
Don't bite me.

16:35.734 --> 16:38.405
(thud in other room)

16:38.439 --> 16:40.309
(barks)

16:48.760 --> 16:52.300
-Okay. (shushing) Come-come on.
-(barks)

16:52.333 --> 16:54.639
-(barks)
-(whispering): Okay, okay.
Shh, shh, shh.

16:54.672 --> 16:56.576
(shushing) Come on, come on.

16:56.609 --> 16:58.245
Come here. Hey, come here,
come here. I got you.

16:58.279 --> 17:00.349
I got you, I got you.
Okay, okay, okay.

17:00.383 --> 17:02.320
Come here. Okay.

17:02.353 --> 17:05.326
Come here. Okay, good boy.
Good boy.

17:07.330 --> 17:10.469
(clears throat)
It's the police.

17:10.504 --> 17:13.342
♪ ♪

17:20.289 --> 17:22.060
(grunting)

17:34.384 --> 17:37.357
-(breathing heavily)
-(grunting)

17:39.427 --> 17:42.100
Oh, no, no.

17:42.133 --> 17:43.703
(straining):
No, no.

17:43.737 --> 17:45.473
No! No!

17:45.507 --> 17:48.813
No! No! No! (grunting)

17:50.651 --> 17:52.554
Oh, shit! (grunts)

17:53.556 --> 17:55.259
(groans)

17:55.293 --> 17:57.330
(breathing heavily)

18:10.590 --> 18:12.393
Yep, what the fuck is right.

18:12.427 --> 18:15.199
Two times, this giant freak
tried to kill me.

18:15.232 --> 18:17.270
Giant freak?

18:17.303 --> 18:20.309
It's the same motherfucker
I shot in Central Park.

18:20.343 --> 18:22.715
-(dog whimpers)
-He was here, in that closet,

18:22.748 --> 18:24.552
and he came for me.

18:24.585 --> 18:27.457
-(snickers)
-What's funny?

18:27.490 --> 18:29.695
What?

18:29.729 --> 18:31.431
GAO:
Nothing. No offense.

18:31.465 --> 18:33.135
Wait outside.

18:33.870 --> 18:36.141
(indistinct chatter
over police radio)

18:37.477 --> 18:38.847
(sighs)

18:38.880 --> 18:41.451
-(door closes)
-So?

18:41.485 --> 18:43.322
"So" what?

18:44.357 --> 18:46.194
Is there anything to it?

18:46.228 --> 18:48.198
Was this just
a little tryst gone wrong?

18:48.232 --> 18:49.835
You're really asking me that?

18:49.869 --> 18:52.641
I never saw this guy before
I shot him in Central Park,

18:52.675 --> 18:54.712
and he was just
in Barbara's closet.

18:54.745 --> 18:56.649
How did he know I was here?

18:56.683 --> 18:58.319
How did he get in?

18:58.352 --> 19:01.793
Did your wife-- sorry, ex-wife--

19:01.826 --> 19:03.897
-know that you were coming here?
-No.

19:03.930 --> 19:07.938
It was not her,
and this was not a lovers' spat.

19:07.971 --> 19:10.744
This guy-- this thing--

19:10.777 --> 19:12.648
came for me,

19:12.681 --> 19:15.353
and I-I don't think
he's gonna stop.

19:15.386 --> 19:17.256
(door closes)

19:18.225 --> 19:19.795
ADAM:
My, uh, my wife is here

19:19.829 --> 19:22.601
for her four-month ultrasound
with Dr. Kornblatt.

19:22.634 --> 19:25.473
She'll be in good hands.
Hello, Mr. Whitely.

19:25.507 --> 19:27.343
Hello, Dianne.

19:28.646 --> 19:30.951
-(knocking)
-(door opens)
-Adam?

19:30.984 --> 19:33.288
I know we hadn't discussed
me being here,

19:33.322 --> 19:35.359
but I got off early
and I thought I'd surprise you.

19:35.393 --> 19:37.831
Dr. Kornblatt,
good to meet you.

19:37.865 --> 19:39.902
You came at the right moment.
You have a very healthy baby.

19:39.935 --> 19:42.908
-Everything looks
perfectly normal.
-That's great news.

19:42.941 --> 19:44.545
KORNBLATT:
Your wife insisted
on a blood panel.

19:44.578 --> 19:46.816
It's an extensive set of tests.

19:46.849 --> 19:48.252
We don't have all the results
yet, but we should probably

19:48.285 --> 19:49.421
go over the ones we do have.

19:49.454 --> 19:51.391
I'll be right back.

19:55.534 --> 19:57.571
Why is he talking to you
and not me?

19:57.604 --> 19:59.374
And what are you doing?
Why are you here?

19:59.407 --> 20:00.811
What's with these tests?

20:02.447 --> 20:04.284
I had a nightmare last night.

20:04.317 --> 20:07.591
I dreamt I was giving birth
to something with tentacles.

20:07.624 --> 20:09.795
It's because of that stupid
tarot reading, isn't it?

20:09.829 --> 20:12.901
(door opens, closes)

20:15.907 --> 20:18.546
-What are you seeing?
-Nothing.

20:18.580 --> 20:22.554
I'm just noticing you have
a slightly low red cell count.

20:22.588 --> 20:24.558
How low?

20:24.592 --> 20:27.931
KORNBLATT:
It's nothing
to get alarmed about.

20:27.965 --> 20:30.269
Probably just
a slight case of anemia.

20:30.302 --> 20:31.706
We'll do some follow-ups,

20:31.739 --> 20:33.843
get it all sorted out.

20:33.877 --> 20:37.417
-Okay?
-Okay.

20:42.494 --> 20:44.297
What's the matter?

20:45.734 --> 20:47.838
After the fire at the bar,

20:47.871 --> 20:49.875
when I took blood samples
from the burn victims

20:49.909 --> 20:51.779
at the hospital,

20:51.813 --> 20:54.317
they all had
low red blood cell counts.

20:54.350 --> 20:55.854
Including me?

20:58.459 --> 21:01.833
I wasn't sure if the results
had been corrupted

21:01.866 --> 21:03.736
or if the immune systems
had been affected by the fire.

21:03.770 --> 21:06.341
We were doing more tests.

21:06.374 --> 21:08.880
Then why would you have
the same issue?

21:09.882 --> 21:11.886
That's what I don't understand.

21:14.892 --> 21:16.394
Hey, are you sure
you're up for this?

21:16.428 --> 21:17.798
I can go in on my own.

21:17.831 --> 21:19.400
Yeah, I'm okay.

21:19.434 --> 21:21.739
But, uh, brace yourself,
it's bad.

21:21.772 --> 21:23.308
Okay.

21:24.110 --> 21:26.047
Oh, hey, your lights are,
uh, not...

21:26.081 --> 21:27.751
(dog barking)

21:27.784 --> 21:30.790
(chuckles):
Hi! Aw, my big guy!

21:30.824 --> 21:32.494
What a big boy!

21:32.528 --> 21:33.730
You're so tough.

21:33.763 --> 21:35.332
Oh, God, Patrick.

21:35.366 --> 21:38.071
Was this person following me
to hurt me,

21:38.105 --> 21:40.409
or to get to you?

21:40.442 --> 21:42.079
I don't know.

21:42.113 --> 21:43.750
Let's get you some clothes.

21:43.783 --> 21:45.654
No, no, no. Don't bother.
I'm staying here.

21:45.687 --> 21:47.423
What? No, you can't.

21:47.456 --> 21:49.895
No, no, no. I don't want to go
to a motel, or worse,

21:49.929 --> 21:51.699
my sister's or anywhere else.

21:51.732 --> 21:54.538
I want to stay in my own home.

21:54.572 --> 21:57.410
-God.
-I don't think
that's a good idea, Barb.

21:57.443 --> 21:59.915
You told me the cops swept
the building, right?

21:59.949 --> 22:01.384
There's a police cruiser parked
right out front.

22:01.418 --> 22:02.654
Yeah, they'll be outside
all night.

22:02.688 --> 22:04.090
Right, well,
then I'm safer here

22:04.123 --> 22:05.694
than probably anywhere else
in the whole city.

22:05.727 --> 22:07.531
Plus, I've got this guy, right?

22:07.564 --> 22:09.033
-(barks)
-To protect me.

22:09.067 --> 22:10.670
Come here, buddy. Look at this.

22:10.704 --> 22:12.106
I'm gonna be perfectly fine.

22:12.139 --> 22:13.843
I just have to give him a name.

22:13.877 --> 22:15.914
I love you.

22:15.947 --> 22:18.786
So, uh, what does
the low red blood count mean?

22:18.820 --> 22:20.389
She said it's harmless for now,

22:20.422 --> 22:22.393
but it's showing up
in everyone's blood work,

22:22.426 --> 22:23.863
including her own.

22:23.897 --> 22:25.834
Is it something
I need to worry about?

22:25.867 --> 22:27.538
The only thing
you need to worry about...

22:27.571 --> 22:29.808
-Hey.
-...is saving room for dinner.

22:29.842 --> 22:31.779
-(chuckles)
-(groans)

22:33.482 --> 22:34.685
Come on.

22:34.718 --> 22:36.454
I've got a surprise.

22:38.960 --> 22:39.962
So...

22:39.995 --> 22:41.464
after you told me what happened,

22:41.499 --> 22:42.834
I thought you and I could
come together

22:42.868 --> 22:44.872
for a more positive experience.

22:44.905 --> 22:47.476
You know, uh, maybe she can tell
us more about our relationship.

22:47.511 --> 22:49.548
You're out of your fucking head.
I'm not going back in there.

22:49.582 --> 22:51.552
Come on, I loved
that whole Death card thing.

22:51.586 --> 22:52.854
You can't deny me that.

22:52.888 --> 22:54.123
Maybe it's some kind of
joke to you,

22:54.157 --> 22:55.560
but it really
freaked Hannah out.

22:55.594 --> 22:57.564
-Gave her nightmares.
-(groans)

22:57.598 --> 22:59.100
Now you're only making this
easier for me.

22:59.133 --> 23:00.436
Come on.

23:03.610 --> 23:05.112
(entry bell chimes)

23:06.649 --> 23:08.185
-(door closes)
-(entry bell chimes)

23:08.218 --> 23:10.523
My boyfriend's an asshole,
that's why I'm back.

23:10.557 --> 23:13.830
After Adam told me about the
reading you gave him and Hannah,

23:13.863 --> 23:15.967
I knew I had to see you
in action for myself.

23:16.001 --> 23:17.971
I'm really glad
to see you again.

23:18.005 --> 23:19.708
You left in such a hurry,
I couldn't tell you

23:19.742 --> 23:21.144
how bad I felt about everything.

23:21.177 --> 23:23.750
It was not done on purpose.

23:23.783 --> 23:25.587
I'd actually feel better
if you told me

23:25.620 --> 23:28.058
it was all some sick scam,
but...

23:28.091 --> 23:29.929
-okay.
-Great, bygones.

23:29.962 --> 23:31.464
Can we get a reading?

23:31.499 --> 23:33.201
That's what I'm here for.

23:33.235 --> 23:35.472
♪ ♪

23:50.637 --> 23:53.876
-No instructions this time?
-I've had so many customers,

23:53.910 --> 23:55.714
I could draw this deck
from memory.

23:56.782 --> 23:58.720
I can do a dual reading.

24:00.055 --> 24:02.527
Each one of you will
cut the deck once.

24:07.203 --> 24:09.742
♪ ♪

24:23.201 --> 24:25.205
♪ ♪

24:40.035 --> 24:43.208
Oof,
that doesn't look very good.

24:43.241 --> 24:46.247
It suggests self-evaluation.

24:46.281 --> 24:47.684
An awakening.

24:47.718 --> 24:50.924
It's a great card.

24:55.032 --> 24:56.802
THEO:
Hmm.

24:56.836 --> 24:59.608
It's not the first time
I've been called the Devil.

24:59.641 --> 25:01.679
(chuckles) I like your attitude.

25:01.712 --> 25:04.017
The Devil can be
playful and fun.

25:04.050 --> 25:07.824
He represents
the questioning intellectual.

25:12.734 --> 25:15.239
♪ ♪

25:15.272 --> 25:17.043
(objects rattling)

25:17.076 --> 25:19.280
Who's gonna die?

25:19.313 --> 25:20.550
(demonic voice):
You!

25:21.619 --> 25:22.721
ADAM:
What is this?

25:22.754 --> 25:24.257
It's just the subway.

25:24.290 --> 25:25.593
It's right beneath us.

25:25.627 --> 25:26.862
Easy, baby, it's the A train.

25:26.896 --> 25:29.100
No, what is that voice?

25:29.133 --> 25:30.837
What voice?

25:30.870 --> 25:32.708
FRAN:
Do you want me to get a new deck

25:32.741 --> 25:34.778
-and-and start from scratch?
-(door closes)

25:34.812 --> 25:36.582
No, no, no. Sorry.

25:36.615 --> 25:37.684
Sorry.

25:38.619 --> 25:40.724
-(door opens)
-(entry bell chimes)

25:40.757 --> 25:42.093
(door closes)

25:54.651 --> 25:56.689
-(phone ringing)
-(busy chatter)

26:01.766 --> 26:04.103
Welcome back, Gino.

26:04.137 --> 26:05.607
You're looking like yourself
again.

26:05.640 --> 26:07.143
After all the shit
I've been through,

26:07.176 --> 26:09.180
who would've thought that fleas
would be the thing

26:09.213 --> 26:10.884
to send me to the hospital?

26:12.186 --> 26:14.090
Don't worry,
I had the place fumigated.

26:18.331 --> 26:20.035
How you doing?

26:20.068 --> 26:23.041
That Fran
who's been working here,

26:23.074 --> 26:25.914
she's, uh, moonlighting as
a psychic on Christopher Street.

26:25.947 --> 26:27.049
She scared my friend
the other day,

26:27.082 --> 26:28.786
and I-I just went back again,

26:28.820 --> 26:32.193
and-and it was just... weird.

26:32.226 --> 26:34.030
Adam, you don't actually think

26:34.063 --> 26:36.902
that she's really a psychic,
do you?

26:36.936 --> 26:38.138
She's got this thing.

26:38.171 --> 26:39.908
I don't know how she does it,

26:39.942 --> 26:41.645
but she-she connects
with your fears

26:41.679 --> 26:43.014
and then lays them out
on the table in front of you.

26:43.983 --> 26:45.954
Your fears?

26:45.987 --> 26:48.793
You'd have to see it
for yourself.

26:50.395 --> 26:52.333
Sounds like a scam.

26:52.366 --> 26:53.936
What if she's right?

26:53.970 --> 26:56.174
What if we're all doomed?

27:00.349 --> 27:02.654
-(door closes)
-(entry bell chimes)

27:04.691 --> 27:05.794
-FRAN: Gino?
-Hey, Fran.

27:05.827 --> 27:07.329
What are you doing here?

27:07.363 --> 27:09.802
Oh, what's the matter,
you-you can't read my mind?

27:09.835 --> 27:11.371
(chuckles):
Oh, you two know each other.

27:11.404 --> 27:12.707
I had no idea.

27:12.741 --> 27:14.210
Huh.

27:14.243 --> 27:16.347
Well, there's no
tougher customer than I,

27:16.381 --> 27:19.053
and Fran is
a gifted clairvoyant.

27:19.086 --> 27:21.057
Uh, I know Fran all too well.

27:21.090 --> 27:24.096
I'm-I'm pretty sure
she's not a psychic.

27:24.130 --> 27:27.002
And you,
you claim to care,

27:27.036 --> 27:29.207
but then you're over here
running a scam,

27:29.240 --> 27:31.077
taking advantage of people's
pain to make a quick buck.

27:31.110 --> 27:32.346
What's wrong with you people?

27:32.379 --> 27:36.689
Gino, I can run any business
I please.

27:36.722 --> 27:38.693
I'm serving the community.

27:38.726 --> 27:42.701
My bathhouse and my tarot shop
are holistic enterprises.

27:42.734 --> 27:44.370
Oh, this-this is ridiculous.

27:44.403 --> 27:46.407
Well, if you don't believe it,
sit down for a reading.

27:46.441 --> 27:49.247
I'm not gonna waste my time
with this nonsense.

27:50.282 --> 27:52.253
What are you afraid of?

27:52.286 --> 27:55.727
Excuse m...
I'm not afraid of anything.

27:55.760 --> 27:57.429
Then sit down.

27:57.463 --> 27:58.733
Fran, take your lunch.

27:58.766 --> 28:00.937
I got this.

28:09.053 --> 28:12.761
(train tracks rattling nearby)

28:12.794 --> 28:15.065
(electrical crackling)

28:22.146 --> 28:24.718
As you can see,

28:24.751 --> 28:26.755
we use a standard tarot deck.

28:26.789 --> 28:28.726
78 cards.

28:28.759 --> 28:30.395
Every card has
a different meaning.

28:30.429 --> 28:31.765
Yeah, I know how tarot works.

28:31.799 --> 28:33.736
Well, then you should also know

28:33.769 --> 28:35.873
that the fate of the cards is
in your hands.

28:40.182 --> 28:42.286
Cut the deck.

28:55.980 --> 28:58.886
♪ ♪

29:18.391 --> 29:19.427
Sorry.

29:21.264 --> 29:23.468
-Let's try this again.
-(cards shuffle)

29:24.504 --> 29:28.144
Shuffle the cards and turn them
over yourself this time.

29:35.158 --> 29:37.329
(cards shuffle)

29:47.550 --> 29:49.821
♪ ♪

30:07.156 --> 30:09.260
(crackling)

30:12.032 --> 30:13.869
You're an angry man, Gino,

30:13.903 --> 30:16.542
and your life is spinning
out of control.

30:16.575 --> 30:18.311
(echoing):
You tell yourself
this anger is caused

30:18.345 --> 30:20.015
by the state of the world,

30:20.048 --> 30:22.419
but you know it's
because you are dying.

30:22.453 --> 30:24.925
Everyone around you is dying.

30:24.958 --> 30:27.296
I can smell it.

30:27.329 --> 30:29.400
I can smell the decay.

30:29.433 --> 30:33.576
It's a black hole sucking in
everything and everyone.

30:33.609 --> 30:36.047
You want to save everyone,

30:36.080 --> 30:38.886
but you're just a scared
little boy yourself,

30:38.919 --> 30:42.192
someone who desperately
wants to be loved.

30:42.226 --> 30:44.397
Do you think anyone can love you

30:44.430 --> 30:47.136
when you have no soul to love?

30:48.471 --> 30:50.042
Turn around, Gino.

30:50.075 --> 30:52.146
(rattling)

30:54.216 --> 30:56.187
Someone wants to meet you.

31:00.897 --> 31:03.001
(echoing):
Shall I kiss you?

31:03.034 --> 31:07.577
Shall I kiss you
and make this all go away?

31:07.610 --> 31:10.015
♪ ♪

31:11.919 --> 31:13.421
(panting)

31:13.455 --> 31:15.158
No!

31:17.362 --> 31:18.933
(breathing shakily)

31:18.966 --> 31:20.937
This is all an illusion.

31:20.970 --> 31:24.176
I... I have a soul.

31:25.646 --> 31:28.084
I know what love is.

31:28.118 --> 31:30.222
(echoing):
The only illusion is
that you think

31:30.255 --> 31:31.625
you can escape your destiny.

31:31.658 --> 31:33.596
(whispering):
I love Patrick.

31:33.629 --> 31:35.600
And Patrick loves me.

31:35.633 --> 31:37.604
(echoing):
How can he even know you?

31:37.637 --> 31:39.306
But don't fret.

31:39.340 --> 31:41.110
He's dying, too.

31:41.144 --> 31:43.314
Stop!

31:45.953 --> 31:47.657
(sighs)

31:47.690 --> 31:50.328
(panting softly)

31:56.040 --> 31:58.344
-(door opens, closes)
-(entry bell chimes)

31:58.378 --> 32:00.583
(gasps) Oh.

32:17.617 --> 32:19.654
(Iggy & The Stooges' "Gimme
Danger (Bowie Mix)" playing)

32:19.688 --> 32:21.925
♪ ♪

32:35.385 --> 32:39.126
♪ Give me danger,
little stranger ♪

32:39.160 --> 32:42.734
♪ And I feel with you at ease ♪

32:42.767 --> 32:46.240
♪ Give me danger,
little stranger ♪

32:46.274 --> 32:49.748
♪ And I'll feel your disease ♪

32:49.781 --> 32:53.154
♪ There's nothing in my dreams ♪

32:53.188 --> 32:57.262
♪ Just some ugly memories ♪

32:57.296 --> 33:01.270
♪ Kiss me like
the ocean breeze ♪

33:03.041 --> 33:05.278
♪ Yeah! ♪

33:08.418 --> 33:12.192
♪ Now, if you will be my lover ♪

33:12.226 --> 33:15.566
♪ I will shiver and sing ♪

33:15.600 --> 33:18.772
♪ But if you can't be
my master ♪

33:18.806 --> 33:22.714
♪ I will do anything ♪

33:22.747 --> 33:26.254
♪ There's nothing left alive ♪

33:26.287 --> 33:30.028
♪ But a pair of glassy eyes ♪

33:30.763 --> 33:34.704
♪ Raise my feelings
one more time ♪

33:35.773 --> 33:37.309
♪ Yeah! ♪

33:40.783 --> 33:43.221
♪ Yeah, find a little stranger ♪

33:43.254 --> 33:45.191
♪ Find a little stranger ♪

33:45.225 --> 33:48.264
♪ Say you're gonna
feel my hand ♪

33:48.298 --> 33:50.035
♪ Say, gotta give me danger ♪

33:50.068 --> 33:52.139
♪ Wild little stranger ♪

33:52.172 --> 33:55.078
♪ Oh, honey,
gonna feel my hand ♪

33:55.111 --> 33:59.220
♪ Swear you're gonna
feel my hand ♪

33:59.253 --> 34:01.792
-♪ Swear you're gonna
feel my hand ♪
-(muffled screaming)

34:12.412 --> 34:14.483
♪ ♪

34:17.289 --> 34:20.362
♪ Give me... ♪

34:20.395 --> 34:22.734
Barb, it's me.

34:22.767 --> 34:24.436
(door closes)

34:24.470 --> 34:29.346
♪ Little stranger ♪

34:31.417 --> 34:36.360
♪ Give me danger ♪

34:38.532 --> 34:44.376
♪ Little stranger ♪

34:46.180 --> 34:51.390
♪ Give me danger ♪

34:52.560 --> 34:58.204
-♪ Little stranger ♪
-Barb.

34:58.237 --> 35:00.743
♪ ♪

35:00.776 --> 35:06.320
♪ Give me danger ♪

35:07.322 --> 35:11.832
-♪ Little stranger ♪
-Whoa. (grunting)

35:11.865 --> 35:15.271
-She's fucking dead.
-What are you talking about?

35:15.305 --> 35:18.277
-She's fucking dead!
-(overlapping shouting)

35:19.881 --> 35:22.587
-Calm down, sir.
-You fucking son of a bitch!

35:22.620 --> 35:24.156
You fucking son of a bitch!

35:24.189 --> 35:27.797
♪ Danger ♪

35:29.868 --> 35:33.408
♪ Gotta feel the pain ♪

35:36.314 --> 35:39.521
♪ You gotta feel the pain ♪

35:40.488 --> 35:44.296
♪ You gotta feel it ♪

35:44.330 --> 35:48.706
♪ Little stranger. ♪

35:49.741 --> 35:52.513
(muffled shouting in distance)

36:02.600 --> 36:05.840
(men whimpering, crying)

36:08.478 --> 36:11.518
(Whitely shushing)

36:13.354 --> 36:15.358
The sedatives will kick in soon.

36:15.392 --> 36:17.497
(men crying)

36:17.530 --> 36:19.333
It's not as bad as it looks.

36:21.370 --> 36:22.974
I know what you're thinking:

36:23.007 --> 36:25.478
"How could it possibly get
any worse?"

36:26.948 --> 36:28.719
Well, it could be for nothing,

36:28.752 --> 36:30.756
which is worse.

36:30.790 --> 36:33.495
-(man cries)
-(sets tools down)

36:33.529 --> 36:36.568
You don't understand,
you don't have the full picture.

36:36.601 --> 36:40.576
-And that... that's my fault.
-(man whimpers)

36:40.609 --> 36:43.916
This isn't about
taking your life.

36:43.949 --> 36:46.521
It's about giving your life
meaning.

36:46.555 --> 36:47.924
(man crying)

36:47.957 --> 36:49.460
It's about being
a part of something,

36:49.494 --> 36:51.531
something that's bigger
than yourself,

36:51.565 --> 36:53.869
something that's important.

36:55.840 --> 36:58.277
You and I,

36:58.311 --> 37:00.683
we're gonna change this city.

37:00.716 --> 37:03.622
I'm just so glad
I can finally talk about it.

37:03.655 --> 37:07.229
-(crying)
-God,

37:07.262 --> 37:09.466
I've been on my own
for so long,

37:09.501 --> 37:12.205
I'm starting to go crazy.

37:13.642 --> 37:14.944
In two weeks' time,

37:14.978 --> 37:17.382
New York will hold
its annual Pride parade.

37:17.416 --> 37:19.420
The city proclaims to the world
that it's

37:19.453 --> 37:22.827
a welcoming place
to all of its gay citizens.

37:22.860 --> 37:24.764
That everyone has a place here.

37:24.798 --> 37:29.641
That all are safe and protected
by its institutions.

37:29.674 --> 37:31.945
That no one is left behind.

37:32.880 --> 37:36.521
Some people actually
believe that shit.

37:36.555 --> 37:38.992
-(whimpering)
-And so,

37:39.026 --> 37:43.034
this year, I've decided that
the parade will mean something.

37:43.067 --> 37:45.840
For the first time,

37:45.873 --> 37:48.377
it will be honest.

37:48.411 --> 37:50.950
Let me show you. (sighs sharply)

37:55.759 --> 37:58.264
(gears creaking)

38:03.341 --> 38:04.811
(gasping)

38:04.844 --> 38:07.415
(crying)

38:10.723 --> 38:12.727
♪ ♪

38:14.898 --> 38:18.572
(crying)

38:24.116 --> 38:26.453
(gears stop)

38:28.057 --> 38:30.729
(crying, whimpering)

38:33.535 --> 38:35.906
It will be honest because...

38:35.940 --> 38:37.910
he will be there.

38:37.944 --> 38:39.881
He's our change.

38:39.914 --> 38:42.018
Our protector.

38:43.020 --> 38:44.524
A sentinel.

38:44.557 --> 38:47.830
Made from the people
this city despises.

38:49.366 --> 38:52.773
They will be transformed,
as you will be,

38:52.807 --> 38:55.513
into agents of change.

38:55.546 --> 39:00.455
So, you see,
it isn't as bad as it looks.

39:00.488 --> 39:02.894
He's almost ready,

39:02.927 --> 39:05.365
but he's missing
two very important parts:

39:05.398 --> 39:08.672
the seat of the soul

39:08.705 --> 39:11.143
and the heat of the loins.

39:11.176 --> 39:13.515
(crying)

39:15.519 --> 39:17.355
Now...

39:19.694 --> 39:22.833
(crying)

39:25.438 --> 39:28.579
Decisions, decisions.

